MOPSLinux installer: procedure order

+0. Greeting
1. Language select (omit for now)
2. Disk partitioning (omit for now, will be from console)
+ 3. Selecting, formatting and activating swap partitions
+ 4. Selecting filesystem mount points
+	4a. Root filesystem
	4b. Other filesystems
	4c. Mounting all filesystems
5. Running package manager selection tool (almost ready)
6. Committing install (performing actual installations)
7. Syncronize database
8. Performing initial system configuration
	8.1. Timezone
	8.2. Optional proprietary drivers installation (NVidia, ATI, etc - which is included in the system or supplied by additional disc)
	8.3. Network
	8.4. Services
	8.5. X.Org
		8.5.1. Video driver
		8.5.2. Mode configuration (automatic/manual)
			8.5.2.1 If manual, resolution
			8.5.2.2 If manual, default depth
		8.5.3. Default window manager
	8.6. Root password
	8.7. Adding users
	8.8. Default login behavior
9. Configuring and installing boot loader
10. Finish setup.
